OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1784839668
OL,3,CAfghan man jailed for two years for
OL,4,Cpiloting dinghy in Channel for two
OL,5,Chours
OL,7,FIn mitigation, barrister Kiera Vinall
OL,8,Fsaid the defendant had to flee from
OL,9,Fthe Taliban in Afghanistan and that is
OL,10,Fwhy he made the crossing, as many
OL,11,Fothers do, "in the hope of a better
OL,12,Flife".
OL,14,FThe court heard he spent his entire
OL,15,Flife savings on the crossing, and
OL,16,Fintends to apply for asylum which he
OL,17,Fhas found difficult as he speaks no
OL,18,FEnglish and is in custody.
OL,26,@sD@LOUtD@EO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
